- starship. The problem is getting it installed because the installer script requires input and apt-get doesn't work for it.
curl -sS https://starship.rs/install.sh | sh
```
$ cat ~/.config/starship.toml
format = """$username$env_var$directory$git_branch$git_status
\\$ """

[username]
show_always = true
format = "[$user](bold yellow)@"

[env_var.THOPTER_NAME]
format = "[$env_value](bold green) "

[hostname]
disabled = true
```

note user recommended iterm2 changes:
- enable "Applications in terminal may access Clipboard."
- enable "copy to clipboard on selection"
- enable "mirror tmux paste buffer to clipoard"

